text: Crisp County is a county in the center of the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, the population was 20,128. The county seat is Cordele. The county was created on August 17, 1905. ==References== Category:1905 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
title: Crisp County, Georgia
